               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18651218-name-30" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18651218-name-30" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18651218-name-30" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18651218-name-30" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a butchers' cutler, of 91, St. John-street, Clerken<lb></lb>well—on 9th December I was passing through Tylor's-market about half-past 3—I had a parcel under my arm and a child's toy in the other hand—I felt the prisoner with his hand pulling at my watch-guard—I seized hold of his hand with my chain round two of his fingers—he never offered to get away, but still kept pulling at my guard—I asked him what he was doing—he said he either wanted to break it, or to have it—he did not succeed in getting it—there was a constable close by, and I gave him in charge—I thought the man was foolish.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
